<div id="review_4025148900" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4025148900" />
    <a title="michal k-c" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100556965-michal-k-c"><img alt="michal k-c" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628875888p2/100556965.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4025148900?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="michal k-c" class="user" itemprop="url" name="michal k-c" href="/user/show/100556965-michal-k-c">michal k-c</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4025148900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15438049818999266420">not sure what Foucault did to earn the reputation of being an incomprehensible postmodernist (mots et les choses, maybe). This is super lucid and readable. I won&apos;t say it&apos;s outdated but since its publication there have been a number of carceral episodes that I feel like really stretch the limits of Foucault&apos;s structuralist analysis here (consider Abu Ghraib and Obama&apos;s &quot;we tortured some folks&quot; comment). Still, not impossible to work within the framework outlined here - American empire leaving th</span>
  <span id="freeText15438049818999266420" style="display:none">not sure what Foucault did to earn the reputation of being an incomprehensible postmodernist (mots et les choses, maybe). This is super lucid and readable. I won't say it's outdated but since its publication there have been a number of carceral episodes that I feel like really stretch the limits of Foucault's structuralist analysis here (consider Abu Ghraib and Obama's "we tortured some folks" comment). Still, not impossible to work within the framework outlined here - American empire leaving the disciplinary mark of the sovereign on the body of the global socius. Good summer read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15438049818999266420" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
