<span id="freeTextContainer6475287437537003375">This was an interesting book, but very dry and over my head at times. There were times I feel like you have to know about French history and French prisons to fully get this book. I think I made mistake reading this book first. I wouldn&apos;t recommended it unless you have a strong interest for philosophy, criminology, and/or French history. It&apos;s obvious Foucault was channeling Marx, Rousseau, and de Sade in this book (he never talks about de Sade, but it reminded me of de Sade&apos;s philosophy). I&apos;m st</span>
